\cf2 Essentially, the user control the Magic Man character with the arrow keys of the computer. He has various magical powers and is trying to save as many people from life as a frog as he can but he only has six minutes. He can gain back 25 seconds by collecting clocks items spawned in around the map and can slow down time by collecting snowflakes. These snowflakes also allow the user to use Magic man\'92s magical powers to become Snow Man who can shoot snowballs that are capable of destroying traps. When the user has the snowman power up they can shoot snowballs with the control button. Unfortunately, hitting these traps not only causes time to speed up but also force Magic Man to pause and subtracts an additional 50 seconds from the total time remaining. The traps also cause magic man to drop all of the magic dust that he is carrying. This magic dust is the source of Magic Man\'92s powers and without it he cannot perform his magic. He needs at least 5 dust clumps to transform one frog back to a person and needs one to shoot a snowball when he has the Snow Man power up. If you can manage to save ten people from life as a frog Magic Man saves the day and you win!! Otherwise, America's population will be entirely made up of frogs.\'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280\partightenfactor0
